  "description": "Three EBs from three distinct pipeline slots (100, 200, 300) are offered, and their vote batches arrive in non-monotonic slot order. The pattern is: offer all three EBs first, then votes for slot 100, then votes for slot 200, then a second batch for slot 100 (returning to an earlier slot), then a second batch for slot 300, then a second batch for slot 200, then a final batch for slot 300. Each EB receives 20 distinct voters across its two batches. A conforming node must maintain independent per-(slot, eb_hash) vote accumulators and correctly attribute late-arriving batches to their proper slot regardless of arrival order. An implementation that only tracks the 'current' pipeline slot, or that flushes vote state when votes for a newer slot arrive, would miscount the tallies for slots 100 and 200. The verifier should observe three separate VotesReceived events per EB and final tallies of 20 for each.",
